{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh chillies and boiling water into it. Soak chillies in boiling water (approx. 10 minutes), then drain and set aside.","Place cumin seeds and coriander seeds into mixing bowl and roast <b>4 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Allow to cool for 5 minutes, then blend <b>3 sec\/speed 9<b> ","Add garlic and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 20 g of the oil and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b> ","Add drained chillies, salt and remaining 20 g oil and blend <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a sealable jar or container and place into refrigerator until ready to use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g fresh red chillies (approx. 9 chillies), cut into pieces","600 g boiling water","2 ½ tsp cumin seeds","2 tsp coriander seeds","5 garlic cloves","40 g extra virgin olive oil","1 tsp salt"]}],"id":"r112526","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-k7xSfepfXog\/XZaqynHK4oI\/AAAAAAAAhhA\/BwSw8JwV6xgOVt_IlRby2Qsj_BZpxbaLQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nUeqipZRdBejAtNt.png","title":"Harissa","publishedAt":"2016-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.2 g","fat":"46.5 g","uom":"per 1 total recipe","carbohydrates":"15.6 g","calories":"2809 kJ \/ 669 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, sealable storage jar or container","hintsAndTricks":["Harissa is a spicy paste often used in North African and Middle Eastern cooking. However, you can reduce the heat by deseeding some of the chillies before soaking in step 1.","Store harissa in a sealable jar or container in the refrigerator for up to 1 month.","You can use dried chillies in this recipe. Simply soak in boiling water for 1 hour before using in step 6 (and omit fresh chillies).","This recipe makes 345 g total."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","25m","1 total recipe"]}